    <a href="#s5"><span class="num">V</span>Contact</a>
  </div>
</nav>

<main>

  <section id="s1">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="section-num">I</span>
      <h2>Overview &amp; Scope</h2>
    </div>
    <p>This Privacy Policy applies when you use the Gearsh mobile application or website to request, book, or receive entertainment services.</p>
    <p>It applies specifically to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Clients</strong> who book Artists through Gearsh</li>
      <li><strong>Artists</strong> who offer services through Gearsh</li>
      <li><strong>Guest Users</strong> who receive services booked by another User</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="note">Our privacy practices may vary depending on applicable laws in the country or region where you use Gearsh.</div>
  </section>

  <section id="s2">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="section-num">II</span>
      <h2>Data Collection &amp; Use</h2>
    </div>

    <h3>A. Data We Collect</h3>
    <p>Gearsh collects personal information in three ways: information you provide, information collected when you use the platform, and information received from third parties.</p>

    <h4>1. Data You Provide</h4>

    <h4>a. Account Information</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Full name</li>
      <li>Email address</li>
      <li>Phone number</li>
      <li>Login credentials</li>
      <li>Profile photo</li>
      <li>Payment method details (processed securely by third-party providers)</li>
      <li>User preferences and settings</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>b. Demographic Information</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Age or date of birth (to verify eligibility)</li>
      <li>Gender (optional, where relevant for analytics or features)</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>c. Identity Verification Information</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Government-issued ID (ID card, passport, or equivalent)</li>
      <li>Selfie or photo for verification</li>
      <li>Verification status (displayed as a verification tick)</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>d. User Content</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Ratings and reviews</li>
      <li>Feedback and support messages</li>
      <li>Uploaded images or documents</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>2. Data Collected When You Use Gearsh</h4>

    <h4>a. Location Data</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Approximate and/or precise location (with permission)</li>
      <li>Event location and Artist location</li>
    </ul>
    <p>This data is used to calculate distance, display maps during booking, and automatically calculate travel and accommodation costs.</p>

    <h4>b. Booking &amp; Transaction Information</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Booking details (date, time, location)</li>
      <li>Distance travelled</li>
      <li>Fees paid and payout amounts</li>
      <li>Cancellation history</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>c. Usage &amp; Device Data</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>App usage statistics</li>
      <li>Device type, operating system, and IP address</li>
      <li>Log and crash data</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>d. Communications Data</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Messages exchanged via the platform</li>
      <li>Support communications</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>3. Data from Third Parties</h4>
    <p>Gearsh may receive data from payment processors, identity verification providers, fraud prevention services, and law enforcement or regulators where legally required.</p>

    <h3>B. How We Use Personal Information</h3>
    <p>Gearsh uses personal data to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Create and manage user accounts</li>
      <li>Enable bookings between Clients and Artists</li>
      <li>Calculate pricing, distance, and additional costs</li>
      <li>Process payments and payouts</li>
      <li>Verify identity and prevent fraud</li>
      <li>Provide customer support</li>
      <li>Improve platform performance and features</li>
      <li>Communicate policy updates and service notices</li>
      <li>Comply with legal and regulatory obligations</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>C. Core Automated Processes</h3>
    <p>Gearsh uses automated systems to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Match Clients with suitable Artists</li>
      <li>Calculate booking prices and travel costs</li>
      <li>Detect fraudulent or suspicious activity</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="note">These processes are essential to providing a secure and efficient marketplace experience.</div>

    <h3>D. Cookies &amp; Similar Technologies</h3>
    <p>Gearsh uses cookies and similar technologies to authenticate users, remember preferences, analyze platform usage, and improve performance. Users may manage cookie preferences through their device or browser settings.</p>

    <h3>E. Data Sharing &amp; Disclosure</h3>
    <p>Gearsh may share personal information:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>With other Users</strong> — booking-related details (name, event details, location)</li>
      <li><strong>With Service Providers</strong> — payment processors, identity verification partners, cloud hosting and analytics providers</li>
      <li><strong>For Legal Reasons</strong> — compliance with laws, court orders, or regulatory requests; investigation of fraud, disputes, or safety incidents</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="highlight-box">Gearsh does not sell personal information.</div>

    <h3>F. Data Retention &amp; Deletion</h3>
    <p>Gearsh retains personal data only as long as necessary to provide services, meet legal, tax, and regulatory requirements, and resolve disputes or enforce agreements.</p>
    <p>Users may request account deletion through the app. Some data may be retained where legally required or necessary for fraud prevention.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="s3">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="section-num">III</span>
      <h2>Choice &amp; Transparency</h2>
    </div>
    <p>Users may:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Access and update personal information</li>
      <li>Control location permissions</li>
      <li>Manage communication preferences</li>
      <li>Request copies of their data</li>
      <li>Request deletion or restriction of processing</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="note">Requests can be made via Gearsh support through the app.</div>
  </section>

  <section id="s4">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="section-num">IV</span>
      <h2>Legal Information</h2>
    </div>

    <h3>A. Data Controller</h3>
    <p>Gearsh is the data controller responsible for personal information processed through the platform.</p>

    <h3>B. Legal Basis for Processing</h3>
    <p>We process personal information based on:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Contractual necessity</li>
      <li>User consent</li>
      <li>Legal obligations</li>
      <li>Legitimate business interests (such as safety and fraud prevention)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>C. Data Transfers</h3>
    <p>Gearsh may process or store data on secure servers located outside your country, subject to appropriate safeguards.</p>

    <h3>D. Updates to This Privacy Policy</h3>
    <p>Gearsh may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Continued use of the platform constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="s5">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="section-num">V</span>
      <h2>Contact</h2>
    </div>
    <p>For privacy-related questions or requests, contact Gearsh support through the app.</p>
  </section>

</main>

<footer>
  <span class="footer-brand">Gearsh</span>
  <div class="footer-links">
    <a href="/privacy" aria-current="page">Privacy Policy</a>
    <a href="/terms.html">Terms &amp; Conditions</a>
  </div>
</footer>

<script>
  const bar = document.getElementById('progress');
  window.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
    const pct = window.scrollY / (document.body.scrollHeight - window.innerHeight) * 100;
    bar.style.width = Math.min(pct, 100) + '%';
  }, { passive: true });
</script>

</body>
</html>
